article.headline: William &amp, Mary 87, Montreat 52
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Chris Darnell and Danny Sumner each scored 16 as William & Mary beat Montreat 87-52 on Saturday. The Tribe (3-6) shot 53.2 percent from the field, overpowering the Cavaliers (5-7) down low. William & Mary had a lopsided 48-4 scoring advantage in the paint. William & Mary led 22-14 with 8:31 remaining in the opening half. By intermission, the Cavaliers were behind 41-24. It didn't get any better in the second half as the Tribe scored 10 straight unanswered points to jump to a 51-24 lead. Aaron Collazo led Montreat with 21 points and Thomas Nicholson added 12. The Cavaliers shot 28.6 from the field. William & Mary doubled Montreat's rebounding total, with 48. David Schneider and Darnell each had six rebounds and Schneider added nine points and had five assists.
